27. Use Flutter Navigation and Routing in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

In Flutter, Navigation and Routing are used to move between different screens (pages) of an app.

Navigation is managed using the Navigator class
Each screen is called a route
Common methods:
Navigator.push() → go to new screen
Navigator.pop() → return to previous screen


💻 Flutter Code Example

//main code
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: FirstScreen(),
    );
  }
}

class FirstScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("First Screen"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: ElevatedButton(
          child: Text("Go to Second Screen"),
          onPressed: () {
            Navigator.push(
              context,
              MaterialPageRoute(builder: (context) => SecondScreen()),
            );
          },
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}

class SecondScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Second Screen"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: ElevatedButton(
          child: Text("Go Back"),
          onPressed: () {
            Navigator.pop(context);
          },
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}